bug.short_desc: [abrt] cinnamon-screensaver-3.2.14-0.4: Process /usr/libexec/cinnamon-screensaver-pam-helper was killed by signal 11 (SIGSEGV)
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/57.0.2987.133 Safari/537.36 Build Identifier:
Cinnamon Screensaver hangs while locking (automatic Lock after x minutes). The screen will turn black just before the locking happens. Afterwards I still can switch to tty2, but not unlock the screen anymore.
The screen shows 90% occupancy a static screensaver-screen and 10% occupancy the Desktop state before locking
Reproducible: Sometimes
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Wait for Screen to be automatically locked Actual Results: Moving mouse and pressing Keys does not modify the screensaver
Expected Results: Moving mouse shows password field and entering password unlocks the screen
I installed Fedora as a Fedora-Spin that included cinnamon as a standard Desktop Environment

Created attachment 1274521 Error Dump
